The Sultan of Sokoto, Sultan Sa’ad Abubakar III, yesterday announced today, Saturday, April 2, 2022, the first day of the holy month of Ramadan. This according to the sultan, followed  the sighting of the moon in almost every part of the country earlier yesterday, the 29th day in the month of Shaban and thereby signified today as the first day of Ramadan 1443AH. He said the moon was sighted in some of  states in the country by Islamic leaders and scholars including Sokoto, Borno, Yobe, Zamfara, Katsina and Plateau among others. Sultan Abubakar urged the entire Muslim faithful in the country to start fast today in accordance with the teachings of Islam. He urged Muslims to use this month of Ramadan  to pray against the spread of banditry and other forms of insecurity in the country He also called for continuous prayers for leaders across the country to tackle the different problems in the country. The sultan advised all Muslims in the country and beyond to observe the fast with ultimate fear of God, saying Muslims in the country should use the period of the fast to pray for peace and unity.